<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-03-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-03-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="267" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d267">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00118 European War (1939)/1807:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">William Phillips</persName>, Personal
                                Representative of President <persName>Roosevelt</persName> in
                                India</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-18">March 18,
                                1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>161. War Department desires to rescind its decision mentioned in
                            Department’s 81, February 9<note n="69" xml:id="d267fn69">Not printed;
                                see airgram No. A–420, February 10, to the Ambassador in the United
                                Kingdom, <ref target="#pg_234">p. 234</ref>.</note> and to obtain
                            for its Observers mentioned therein the status and designation of
                            “Military Observers with Personal rank of Military Attaché and Assistant
                            Military Attachés.” Please inquire whether these assignments will be
                            agreeable to Government of India. Telegraph. Embassy at London
                            informed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>